result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Richard A Hyatt was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Cases called:16CF135 & 15CF495, Defendant Richard A Hyatt in court, in custody with attorney Amanda K. Riek.  Troy D Cross appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties have received PSI, no corrections. Sentence arguments made. In 15CF495, Court sentenced defendant to one year jail, consecutive to 16CF135. $1,769 fine. Sixty days to pay fine or set up a payment plan with Clerk of Courts. 36 month revocation, 36 month IID. Submit DNA sample. 270 days jail credit. Court deemed time served. In 16CF135, defendant sentenced to 4 1/2 years prison: 2 years confinement, 2 1/2 years extended supervision commencing forth with.$1,769 fine. 36 month revocation, 36 month IID. Submit DNA sample.  No possession or consumption of alcoholic beverages.  Submit DNA sample.  Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program, not eligible for Challenge Academy. 128 days jail credit.
Filed by Probation Agent Shannon Whitish.
